narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I definitely enjoyed the course; not too difficult, great professor (Loewenberg). I thought the course could have been more rigorous, then I remembered that I'm a senior chemical engineering major.
Most likely required if you are looking at this class. It's a fine class, workload is not too heavy, and the course is well-run this semester.

This is a requirement for the chemical engineering major, so most people take it for that reason. It isn't difficult if Loewenberg is teaching it, and probably less of a workload than other chemE courses.
